Defendant Jarvis D Griffin in court with attorney Thomas W. Kurzynski.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

The Court ordered defendant to serve 10 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 2 days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges for employment, employment searches or school. Defendant to report by 11/27/2015 by 5:00 p.m.

Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and mandatory surcharges by 1/18/2016. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

